{{DEFAULTSORT:Woodroof, Ron}}
{{Infobox person | name = Ron Woodroof | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = 1950 | birth_place = Texas | death_date = Sept. 12, 1992 | death_place = | occupation = | spouse = | parents = | children = }}
Ron Woodroof created what would become known as the Dallas Buyers Club in March 1988. Contracting HIV in the 1980s, he created the group as part of his efforts to find and distribute drugs to treat HIV at a time when the drug was poorly understood.<ref>http://www.biography.com/people/ron-woodroof-21329541#early-years&</ref> He died on September 12, 1992. <ref>http://www.npr.org/2013/11/01/242309799/the-dallas-cowboy-behind-the-real-buyers-club</ref>
==Biography==
===Death and afterward===
His life was the basis of the 2013 film [[The Dallas Buyers Club]].
